main event: There were multiple sightings of unidentified objects in and around Goose Bay, Labrador in May 1953, including a sighting by a pilot, radar operators, and control tower personnel.
interesting points: The objects were observed to move at high speeds, hover, and then accelerate rapidly, reaching speeds estimated to be over 1000 MPH.
A control tower operator reported that the sighting report had been classified as secret.
The pilot of a commercial airline reported sighting two luminous objects while flying 230 miles SE of Goose Bay.
There was insufficient data for evaluation of a specific sighting on May 25, 1953, where a luminous object was observed at over 7,000 ft for 3-4 minutes.
The reports describe the objects as having variable speeds, ranging from 600 MPH to over 1000 MPH, and exhibiting rapid and erratic movements.
sighted object: multiple unidentified objects, including luminous points and moon-shaped objects
witnesses: pilot, radar operators, control tower personnel, and commercial airline crew
photographs: no photographs available in the report
